Let $X_1, \\ldots, X_n$ be an i.i.d. random sample with probability density function (pdf) 
	\\begin{equation*}
		f(x|\\theta) = \\begin{cases}
			\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{\\pi \\theta}}e^{-\\frac{x^2}{\\theta}}, \\quad &x>0, \\\\
			0, \\quad &\\text{otherwise};
